-- int_deduped_billing_events.sql
```sql
-- Deduplicate billing events per subscription and month
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.subscription_id,
        b.event_month,
        b.amount,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY b.subscription_id, b.event_month
            ORDER BY b.event_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_billing_events') }} AS b
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
FROM source AS src
WHERE src.row_num = 1
```

-- int_enriched_subscriptions.sql
```sql
-- Enriched subscriptions with user, company, and plan dimensions
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        s.subscription_id,
        s.user_id,
        COALESCE(p.tier, '(unknown)') AS tier,
        COALESCE(c.industry, '(unknown)') AS industry
    FROM {{ ref('stg_subscriptions') }} AS s
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_plans') }} AS p
        ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_users') }} AS u
        ON s.user_id = u.user_id
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_companies') }} AS c
        ON u.company_id = c.company_id
)
SELECT
    subscription_id,
    user_id,
    tier,
    industry
FROM source AS src
```

-- fct_monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
```sql
-- Final monthly subscription metrics aggregated by tier and industry
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        b.event_month AS month,
        s.tier,
        s.industry,
        COUNT(b.subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
        SUM(b.amount) AS total_mrr,
        COUNT(DISTINCT s.user_id) AS unique_users
    FROM {{ ref('int_deduped_billing_events') }} AS b
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_enriched_subscriptions') }} AS s
        ON b.subscription_id = s.subscription_id
    GROUP BY
        b.event_month,
        s.tier,
        s.industry
)
SELECT
    month,
    tier,
    industry,
    active_subscriptions,
    total_mrr,
    unique_users
FROM source AS src
